00:00:00,040 --> 00:00:14,740
( Watch on Kissasia.vip )

1
00:00:12,200 --> 00:00:15,098
Dad, Mom, I'm off to school.

2
00:00:17,381 --> 00:00:18,475
Earn.

3
00:00:19,470 --> 00:00:22,618
When is the absolute latest we can pay your tuition?

4
00:00:25,250 --> 00:00:28,245
Can we delay it for another month?

5
00:00:28,952 --> 00:00:32,619
Your dad took the car for repairs today. We don't have insurance.

6
00:00:32,620 --> 00:00:34,837
We're still short tens of thousands for the repair.

7
00:00:35,257 --> 00:00:38,439
Dad and I are rushing to get the money for you, okay?

8
00:00:39,692 --> 00:00:40,812
I'm so sorry.

9
00:00:42,336 --> 00:00:44,411
Dad, Mom.

10
00:00:45,424 --> 00:00:49,149
Can I use my savings to pay for it first?

11
00:00:49,931 --> 00:00:50,938
Earn...

12
00:00:51,726 --> 00:00:53,594
Do you really have that much saved up?

13
00:00:55,309 --> 00:00:58,598
The reason I've been coming home late every day

14
00:00:58,599 --> 00:01:00,944
is because I've been tutoring.

15
00:01:02,801 --> 00:01:05,645
Some days I teach so many people.

16
00:01:05,646 --> 00:01:07,718
You guys don't have to worry.

17
00:01:08,181 --> 00:01:09,901
I like teaching.

18
00:01:10,314 --> 00:01:13,025
And I want to help you both.

19
00:01:15,377 --> 00:01:16,824
Thank you, sweetie.

20
00:01:17,068 --> 00:01:18,621
My smart girl.

21
00:01:19,178 --> 00:01:21,420
I'm so proud to have you.

22
00:01:42,278 --> 00:01:46,839
Pun, why are you turning the sound on? Just watch the video.

23
00:01:46,840 --> 00:01:49,782
Are you stupid? We're going to get caught.

24
00:01:50,282 --> 00:01:51,758
I can't see their faces.

25
00:01:52,069 --> 00:01:54,490
But maybe we can recognize the voice of a student from our school.

26
00:01:55,678 --> 00:01:58,658
Ugh, I've scrolled so much my eyes hurt.

27
00:01:58,659 --> 00:02:01,393
I still haven't found any videos with our school uniform.

28
00:02:02,475 --> 00:02:06,238
I thought they said she were fired for making a video with a student from our school?

29
00:02:06,711 --> 00:02:10,001
Or maybe it was a kid from another school?

30
00:02:10,729 --> 00:02:12,989
Hey, is this it?

31
00:02:14,226 --> 00:02:17,393
Yeah, it looks like our school uniform.

32
00:02:21,388 --> 00:02:23,321
Shit, probably not.

33
00:02:39,048 --> 00:02:40,295
Hey.

34
00:02:46,086 --> 00:02:47,720
The fan meeting seating plan is out.

35
00:02:52,551 --> 00:02:54,948
Should we go for VIP? It's close to the stage.

36
00:02:55,303 --> 00:02:56,409
Yeah.

37
00:02:56,709 --> 00:03:00,420
Let's use the French room, the internet is fast.

38
00:03:00,421 --> 00:03:02,083
Earn can definitely get them.

39
00:03:02,084 --> 00:03:04,551
She's the ticket-buying champion three times in a row, right?

40
00:03:21,049 --> 00:03:24,288
P'Som, could you hide the content where we're in school uniforms first?

41
00:03:24,734 --> 00:03:26,469
I think my friends are getting suspicious.

42
00:03:28,533 --> 00:03:30,699
I might not be able to yet, Earn.

43
00:03:30,700 --> 00:03:34,239
The engagement is really good right now.

44
00:03:37,546 --> 00:03:40,787
Don't overthink it. No one will know.

45
00:03:40,787 --> 00:03:45,147
I'll transfer your cut. We made a lot this round.

46
00:03:45,147 --> 00:03:47,759
Once you see the money, you'll stop worrying.

47
00:03:51,323 --> 00:03:56,357
By the way, when will you agree to do face-reveal content with me?

48
00:03:56,357 --> 00:03:59,028
Fans are sending requests.

49
00:03:59,028 --> 00:04:03,314
If you agree, we can make four times what we did with the uniform video.

50
00:04:07,106 --> 00:04:08,486
Maybe not yet.

51
00:04:21,863 --> 00:04:23,523
Hey, Earn.

52
00:04:23,524 --> 00:04:25,810
Nano borrowed ten thousand from me.

53
00:04:25,811 --> 00:04:29,551
She said if I became the color team president, she'd get the money to pay me back.

54
00:04:29,551 --> 00:04:32,021
But since I didn't get the position, she hasn't returned it.

55
00:04:32,022 --> 00:04:34,470
And the fan meeting ticket sales are coming up.

56
00:04:34,923 --> 00:04:36,656
If she doesn't pay me back...

57
00:04:37,478 --> 00:04:39,642
Earn, do you have some I could borrow first?

58
00:04:40,837 --> 00:04:42,003
Yeah.

59
00:04:42,536 --> 00:04:45,029
I do. Don't worry, Pun.

60
00:04:47,279 --> 00:04:50,076
Has Nano ever borrowed money from you, Earn?

61
00:04:51,200 --> 00:04:53,507
Yeah, she has.

62
00:04:53,508 --> 00:04:55,260
But not that much.

63
00:04:56,341 --> 00:04:57,781
How much is not that much?

64
00:04:58,556 --> 00:05:01,064
About the same as what she borrowed from you.

65
00:05:01,544 --> 00:05:03,106
And has she paid you back yet?

66
00:05:06,143 --> 00:05:08,707
I really want to know what she's doing with the money.

67
00:05:08,708 --> 00:05:11,340
It's been a month, man, and she still hasn't paid me back.

68
00:05:11,340 --> 00:05:12,916
Her family seems rich too, right?

69
00:05:14,911 --> 00:05:17,376
I've seen Nano taking care of a lot of stray cats.

70
00:05:17,377 --> 00:05:20,376
She also mentioned that cat food is really expensive.

71
00:05:20,377 --> 00:05:24,063
She feels sorry for them and doesn't want to leave them on the street.

72
00:05:24,581 --> 00:05:27,188
And her family doesn't support her buying cat food.

73
00:05:28,616 --> 00:05:30,603
Is it really just for raising cats?

74
00:05:41,729 --> 00:05:43,598
Guess who?

75
00:05:44,978 --> 00:05:47,460
Hey, shouldn't I be the one asking that?

76
00:05:53,211 --> 00:05:54,924
I just said it for you.

77
00:05:55,144 --> 00:05:56,524
So you wouldn't have to tire yourself out.

78
00:05:59,278 --> 00:06:00,916
If I didn't want to get tired,

79
00:06:01,182 --> 00:06:02,976
I probably wouldn't have come to see you, right?

80
00:06:13,861 --> 00:06:15,905
I'm really busy today.

81
00:06:15,906 --> 00:06:17,551
I need to hurry up and go.

82
00:06:18,692 --> 00:06:20,339
You're busy every day.

83
00:06:20,732 --> 00:06:22,496
More like you're bored of me.

84
00:06:23,922 --> 00:06:25,308
I'm not bored.

85
00:06:28,961 --> 00:06:30,268
Normally,

86
00:06:31,091 --> 00:06:33,342
I never really think too much about you.

87
00:06:34,265 --> 00:06:38,907
But I don't know why, lately my feelings have been strange.

88
00:06:41,206 --> 00:06:43,681
I mean, we've had this secret thing going on for so long.

89
00:06:44,831 --> 00:06:47,305
And I only do this kind of thing with you.

90
00:06:47,815 --> 00:06:49,195
I think...

91
00:06:51,186 --> 00:06:52,672
I'm catching feelings.

92
00:06:55,372 --> 00:06:58,392
And you probably feel the same way, right?

93
00:07:00,293 --> 00:07:02,153
What you said on that show...

94
00:07:03,228 --> 00:07:05,417
My name is Sasikamol.

95
00:07:06,052 --> 00:07:07,492
It starts with an 'S' too.

96
00:07:09,422 --> 00:07:10,922
Did you mean me?

97
00:07:36,427 --> 00:07:37,527
Earn.

98
00:07:38,160 --> 00:07:39,427
Where's Belle?

99
00:07:41,151 --> 00:07:43,353
She probably went to the restroom.

100
00:07:43,693 --> 00:07:45,805
In the restroom for the whole period?

101
00:07:53,565 --> 00:07:55,999
Here, at the end of the period,

102
00:07:56,000 --> 00:07:58,710
please collect everyone's exercises and leave them at the front of the room.

103
00:07:58,710 --> 00:07:59,882
I'll be right back.

104
00:07:59,883 --> 00:08:01,283
And please hand these out too.

105
00:09:00,324 --> 00:09:01,891
Why aren't you in class?

106
00:09:01,892 --> 00:09:03,138
I don't feel like it.

107
00:09:07,844 --> 00:09:09,450
Smoking is not allowed here.

108
00:09:10,465 --> 00:09:11,671
I know.

109
00:09:12,346 --> 00:09:14,021
But I don't care.

110
00:09:14,128 --> 00:09:16,781
Rules aren't meant to be followed all the time, right?

111
00:09:16,910 --> 00:09:18,625
Learn to follow your heart sometimes.

112
00:09:19,471 --> 00:09:22,321
Do you know how? If not, I can teach you.

113
00:09:34,045 --> 00:09:35,674
Before you try teaching me...

114
00:09:35,767 --> 00:09:37,247
go back to your class.

115
00:10:17,972 --> 00:10:20,353
[Did you transfer money? 20,000 baht?]

116
00:10:24,952 --> 00:10:26,990
[It's my savings from tutoring.]

117
00:10:26,991 --> 00:10:30,357
[I'll give it to Dad for the car repair first. Don't worry.]

118
00:10:42,094 --> 00:10:43,147
Jane.

119
00:10:43,564 --> 00:10:44,724
Are you here to read?

120
00:10:45,855 --> 00:10:47,095
No.

121
00:10:48,328 --> 00:10:50,268
My notebook got torn.

122
00:10:53,784 --> 00:10:56,958
I thought I'd come borrow some tape from the teacher around here to fix it.

123
00:10:57,298 --> 00:10:58,958
I don't know where they are.

124
00:11:02,996 --> 00:11:04,631
Jane, you can tell me anything.

125
00:11:05,866 --> 00:11:08,597
Even though I might not be able to help much,

126
00:11:08,598 --> 00:11:10,203
you can really talk to me.

127
00:11:13,566 --> 00:11:15,046
Thank you, Earn.

128
00:11:17,103 --> 00:11:20,140
I really don't know what I did wrong.

129
00:11:20,640 --> 00:11:23,979
Why do they have to bully me like this?

130
00:11:27,469 --> 00:11:28,629
You're not wrong, Jane.

131
00:11:29,024 --> 00:11:30,557
The people bullying you are.

132
00:11:31,452 --> 00:11:32,599
Don't be discouraged.

133
00:11:36,673 --> 00:11:38,213
Let me see.

134
00:11:41,100 --> 00:11:43,260
It's torn up so badly.

135
00:11:43,553 --> 00:11:47,283
I think I'll go find a big book to press it flat.

136
00:11:47,284 --> 00:11:50,651
Hey, it's okay, I'll go look for one myself.

137
00:11:57,266 --> 00:11:59,735
The encyclopedias are over there.

138
00:12:00,475 --> 00:12:01,780
Oh.

139
00:12:01,781 --> 00:12:03,507
Okay, okay, I'll be right back.

140
00:12:18,735 --> 00:12:20,597
Hey, someone's coming.

141
00:12:20,597 --> 00:12:21,684
Run!

142
00:12:24,699 --> 00:12:25,712
What?

143
00:12:26,379 --> 00:12:27,654
What the...?

144
00:12:29,267 --> 00:12:30,561
What are you doing?

145
00:12:30,830 --> 00:12:33,324
Oh, hi.

146
00:12:35,525 --> 00:12:37,012
Amy, right?

147
00:12:38,629 --> 00:12:41,273
Oh, I went to hear you sing the other day.

148
00:12:41,274 --> 00:12:43,852
Wow, you were really awesome.

149
00:12:43,853 --> 00:12:45,198
Thanks.

150
00:12:48,457 --> 00:12:49,990
Oh, this is my friend.

151
00:12:50,516 --> 00:12:53,449
She just went through a breakup, she's crying.

152
00:12:53,817 --> 00:12:55,117
Cry!

153
00:13:00,360 --> 00:13:02,246
She doesn't really want anyone to see her face.

154
00:13:03,106 --> 00:13:05,509
Okay, okay. I won't bother you guys then.

155
00:13:05,510 --> 00:13:06,936
I'll get going now.

156
00:13:08,758 --> 00:13:10,671
Cheer up!

157
00:13:22,884 --> 00:13:24,637
Your hair is a mess.

158
00:13:24,879 --> 00:13:26,353
Did it look natural?

159
00:13:26,686 --> 00:13:27,726
Maybe.

160
00:13:30,991 --> 00:13:34,044
Sorry I'm late. I ran into someone I knew.

161
00:13:35,170 --> 00:13:37,859
Hmm, you have a friend now, Jane?

162
00:13:37,859 --> 00:13:39,338
We just met.

163
00:13:42,594 --> 00:13:44,053
By the way, Earn,

164
00:13:44,054 --> 00:13:48,111
how do the cheer stand and the cheerleaders usually split the budget?

165
00:13:48,424 --> 00:13:51,448
Actually, other color teams usually split it evenly.

166
00:13:51,449 --> 00:13:55,258
But our team usually wins the cheerleader more than the cheer stand.

167
00:13:55,259 --> 00:13:57,952
So we split it 60/40.

168
00:13:58,445 --> 00:14:01,291
But sometimes even 70.

169
00:14:01,897 --> 00:14:03,151
Whoa!

170
00:14:03,657 --> 00:14:06,321
Why do cheerleaders have so many expenses?

171
00:14:06,322 --> 00:14:10,082
I'm not exactly sure, but from what I've seen,

172
00:14:10,083 --> 00:14:15,936
it's mostly for off-campus practice venues, costumes,

173
00:14:15,937 --> 00:14:19,475
or hair and makeup on the sports day, things like that.

174
00:14:19,476 --> 00:14:21,379
But I don't know about the rest.

175
00:14:23,311 --> 00:14:25,777
Then it's okay. I'll go talk to Nano myself.

176
00:14:28,110 --> 00:14:29,482
Need my help?

177
00:14:56,301 --> 00:14:57,374
Hey!

178
00:14:57,375 --> 00:14:58,507
Watch out!

179
00:14:59,714 --> 00:15:00,780
Shit!

180
00:15:02,668 --> 00:15:03,964
Hey, I'm so sorry.

181
00:15:04,824 --> 00:15:06,101
Does it hurt a lot?

182
00:15:07,576 --> 00:15:09,603
Hey, go get some ice for a cold compress.

183
00:15:20,882 --> 00:15:22,371
Does it hurt a lot?

184
00:15:23,296 --> 00:15:24,904
It doesn't hurt much now.

185
00:15:27,907 --> 00:15:30,221
And I don't feel anything at all.

186
00:15:32,817 --> 00:15:34,890
Do you want to go to the doctor?

187
00:15:42,644 --> 00:15:45,172
Keep the compress on, it won't heal.

188
00:16:16,925 --> 00:16:18,800
There won't be that many people joining the stand anyway.

189
00:16:19,773 --> 00:16:21,649
But then we wouldn't have enough money for cutouts.

190
00:16:21,650 --> 00:16:23,002
Then scale it down.

191
00:16:25,418 --> 00:16:26,943
Then can you give me a breakdown?

192
00:16:26,944 --> 00:16:29,475
What exactly do the cheerleaders need, and how much budget?

193
00:16:31,428 --> 00:16:32,803
Just for the costumes,

194
00:16:32,804 --> 00:16:34,603
we always have to pay out of our own pockets every year.

195
00:16:34,604 --> 00:16:36,304
Not to mention the hair and makeup artists.

196
00:16:36,837 --> 00:16:39,639
All of that already exceeds 70%.

197
00:16:40,292 --> 00:16:41,920
Then you scale it down.

198
00:16:48,148 --> 00:16:49,481
You're determined, aren't you?

199
00:16:49,983 --> 00:16:51,563
The highlight of our school's sports day

200
00:16:52,091 --> 00:16:53,793
is the cheerleaders.

201
00:16:55,016 --> 00:16:57,651
No one wants to scream their lungs out singing cheer songs.

202
00:16:58,618 --> 00:17:01,100
Since you just transferred here, learn to adapt.

203
00:17:03,372 --> 00:17:04,912
Don't be annoying.

204
00:17:11,590 --> 00:17:14,345
Then I'll go ask the juniors who wants to be on the stand.

205
00:17:14,346 --> 00:17:16,371
And I'll calculate the budget based on the actual numbers.

206
00:17:17,208 --> 00:17:18,248
Try me.

207
00:17:27,856 --> 00:17:30,710
This will be what our stand looks like this year.

208
00:17:30,710 --> 00:17:33,506
Time Travel... it can go back in time, like

209
00:17:33,507 --> 00:17:35,995
time machines, dinosaurs, or like

210
00:17:35,996 --> 00:17:40,307
you could dress up as any character from the past.

211
00:17:40,308 --> 00:17:42,944
So whoever wants to be on the stand or wants to help make props,

212
00:17:42,945 --> 00:17:44,471
just let me know.

213
00:17:44,472 --> 00:17:45,792
P'Jane.

214
00:17:45,793 --> 00:17:48,866
If our whole class wants to be on the stand, will there be enough seats?

215
00:17:51,676 --> 00:17:52,779
Wow, the whole class?

216
00:17:52,780 --> 00:17:56,416
Yeah, of course there's enough! Definitely enough. Sure!

217
00:18:00,381 --> 00:18:02,612
So many juniors want to be on the stand.

218
00:18:02,613 --> 00:18:05,662
I guess the cheer budget needs to be doubled.

219
00:18:06,542 --> 00:18:09,023
I don't think 50/50 is going to work anymore.

220
00:18:14,702 --> 00:18:16,210
Hey everyone.

221
00:18:16,211 --> 00:18:19,476
Thank you so much for joining the cheer stand this year.

222
00:18:22,012 --> 00:18:26,549
But with this, we probably won't have much budget left to help the cheerleaders.

223
00:18:27,016 --> 00:18:30,475
But I still want to watch P'Nano and the cheerleaders dance beautifully!

224
00:18:30,476 --> 00:18:33,838
Yeah! The cheerleaders are the pride of our group!

225
00:18:39,370 --> 00:18:41,112
We'll try our best.

226
00:18:41,618 --> 00:18:44,269
But it might not be as grand as previous years.

227
00:19:02,402 --> 00:19:03,870
P'Jane.

228
00:19:03,871 --> 00:19:05,164
What is it?

229
00:19:05,551 --> 00:19:08,837
My friends and I are backing out.

230
00:19:09,143 --> 00:19:12,551
I have friends who are cheerleaders, and I want them to be able to do their best.

231
00:19:12,552 --> 00:19:14,606
If we don't join the stand,

232
00:19:14,607 --> 00:19:17,119
the cheerleaders will get their budget back, right?

233
00:19:18,253 --> 00:19:20,540
Um... yeah.

234
00:19:20,541 --> 00:19:22,326
I'm sorry, P'Jane.

235
00:19:46,896 --> 00:19:49,549
Hello, P'Amy.

236
00:20:00,289 --> 00:20:02,555
We're shooting a school promotional video.

237
00:20:02,556 --> 00:20:03,945
Clip it nicely.

238
00:20:25,423 --> 00:20:26,869
Hello, ma'am.

239
00:20:28,229 --> 00:20:29,793
Oh, hello ma'am.

240
00:20:31,188 --> 00:20:34,075
Hello, teacher. Hello, ma'am.

241
00:20:34,075 --> 00:20:35,229
Thank you.

242
00:20:42,640 --> 00:20:44,273
I just dropped by to say hi to Teacher Thip

243
00:20:44,274 --> 00:20:46,704
and brought some snacks for everyone.

244
00:20:46,705 --> 00:20:48,338
Enjoy.

245
00:20:48,339 --> 00:20:49,884
Thank you.

246
00:20:53,105 --> 00:20:55,581
Amy looks very proper today.

247
00:20:56,347 --> 00:20:58,152
Are you here to receive an award too?

248
00:20:59,937 --> 00:21:03,371
Today, the school selected exemplary student representatives, ma'am.

249
00:21:03,372 --> 00:21:06,553
Both from the academic and extracurricular sides

250
00:21:06,554 --> 00:21:08,854
to shoot a promotional VTR.

251
00:21:09,661 --> 00:21:13,058
Watawan here is the representative for outstanding extracurricular activities.

252
00:21:13,504 --> 00:21:17,301
The song she composed herself is actually going viral right now.

253
00:21:20,329 --> 00:21:22,760
Um, ma'am, excuse me.

254
00:21:22,761 --> 00:21:26,142
If you're ready, could I interview you first?

255
00:21:26,142 --> 00:21:27,478
Sure.

256
00:21:27,479 --> 00:21:28,785
This way, please.

257
00:21:28,786 --> 00:21:30,200
Please.

258
00:21:31,575 --> 00:21:33,569
Ma'am, how important do you think the smart library

259
00:21:33,570 --> 00:21:37,232
is to the education of students like us?

260
00:21:37,232 --> 00:21:39,372
I think it's very important.

261
00:21:39,373 --> 00:21:40,816
Because kids these days

262
00:21:40,817 --> 00:21:43,809
can all find information online.

263
00:21:43,809 --> 00:21:47,549
I probably can't compete with the younger generation when it comes to technology.

264
00:21:47,549 --> 00:21:50,291
So, I'd like to make a contribution

265
00:21:50,291 --> 00:21:54,199
towards purchasing and developing educational equipment.

266
00:21:54,199 --> 00:21:57,090
I'll hand it over to the committee and the teachers

267
00:21:57,091 --> 00:22:01,395
to allocate and purchase for the school.

268
00:22:01,396 --> 00:22:04,000
This contribution I'm making

269
00:22:04,001 --> 00:22:06,566
will hopefully help the students

270
00:22:06,567 --> 00:22:09,081
further their education.

271
00:22:09,082 --> 00:22:11,610
Ma'am, do you have a message for students

272
00:22:11,611 --> 00:22:14,064
who are considering enrolling here?

273
00:22:14,065 --> 00:22:18,004
This is a school that teaches students to be well-mannered

274
00:22:18,005 --> 00:22:21,948
and to be proper young ladies, as they should be.

275
00:22:21,949 --> 00:22:26,788
Come join our Anna Patronage Tipwan family.

276
00:22:27,173 --> 00:22:28,432
For P'Sophie,

277
00:22:28,433 --> 00:22:32,231
how should a proper young lady behave nowadays?

278
00:22:32,689 --> 00:22:35,158
The most important thing for every student,

279
00:22:35,159 --> 00:22:37,603
whether now or in the past,

280
00:22:37,604 --> 00:22:39,658
is simply to know your duties

281
00:22:39,659 --> 00:22:41,791
and fulfill them to the best of your ability,

282
00:22:41,792 --> 00:22:43,814
without causing trouble for anyone.

283
00:22:44,068 --> 00:22:47,174
That, to me, is considered being a proper young lady.

284
00:22:47,175 --> 00:22:48,666
And how does this school help

285
00:22:48,667 --> 00:22:52,498
further students' interests outside of academics?

286
00:22:52,499 --> 00:22:56,303
Actually, our school supports extracurricular activities quite a lot.

287
00:22:56,304 --> 00:22:58,083
But beyond that,

288
00:22:58,084 --> 00:23:01,770
we have a parent association that constantly encourages students

289
00:23:01,771 --> 00:23:06,223
and fully supports us with equipment.

290
00:23:06,224 --> 00:23:09,220
Which I think is a really lovely thing.

291
00:23:09,807 --> 00:23:13,686
Um, computers at other schools might be just for doing reports,

292
00:23:13,687 --> 00:23:17,250
but our school's computers also have music production software installed.

293
00:23:17,251 --> 00:23:19,808
So I consider this award I received today

294
00:23:19,809 --> 00:23:23,381
to be mine and everyone's who helped vote for me.

295
00:23:23,382 --> 00:23:27,278
Including you too, ma'am. Thank you.

296
00:23:27,390 --> 00:23:29,170
Thank you.

297
00:23:32,418 --> 00:23:34,058
This friend of yours is quite nice.

298
00:23:34,623 --> 00:23:37,465
I see her coming over every day for you to tutor her.

299
00:23:37,466 --> 00:23:39,759
I thought she'd be a slacker.

300
00:23:41,414 --> 00:23:43,332
Amy is a smart person.

301
00:23:43,333 --> 00:23:46,869
She might fall behind in class sometimes because she does a lot of activities,

302
00:23:47,449 --> 00:23:49,546
but whatever she's interested in,

303
00:23:49,826 --> 00:23:51,576
she excels at it.

304
00:24:02,847 --> 00:24:04,716
How should we edit this?

305
00:24:05,469 --> 00:24:08,334
There's a part where there's a lot of dead air.

306
00:24:08,334 --> 00:24:11,446
Oh, P'Amy. I thought you had already gone home.

307
00:24:11,447 --> 00:24:14,146
Wow, your answers today were so good!

308
00:24:14,147 --> 00:24:16,594
If I were P'Sophie's mom, I'd be so thrilled.

309
00:24:16,595 --> 00:24:18,413
Wow, really?

310
00:24:18,414 --> 00:24:19,537
Yeah!

311
00:24:19,538 --> 00:24:21,005
Hey, Aioon.

312
00:24:21,006 --> 00:24:23,509
Why don't you let P'Amy help check the pacing of the edit?

313
00:24:23,510 --> 00:24:26,353
I'm going to go lock the club room door first, in case I forget.

314
00:24:26,354 --> 00:24:27,181
Okay.

315
00:24:27,183 --> 00:24:28,421
I'll get going now.

316
00:24:32,776 --> 00:24:35,199
Are you fully recovered?

317
00:24:35,200 --> 00:24:37,124
You're even here helping shoot content today.

318
00:24:37,125 --> 00:24:41,220
It still hurts a bit, but it's okay.

319
00:24:41,221 --> 00:24:42,728
You're so hardworking.

320
00:24:42,729 --> 00:24:44,654
Do you want to be the club president like Anna?

321
00:24:45,747 --> 00:24:50,246
I just wanted to try shooting content, so I came to help.

322
00:24:50,247 --> 00:24:53,330
I like filming when you guys are doing activities.

323
00:24:53,331 --> 00:24:54,639
Really?

324
00:24:54,640 --> 00:24:58,121
So among all the things you've filmed, are there any behind-the-scenes of me?

325
00:25:04,060 --> 00:25:05,508
There's a lot.

326
00:25:07,442 --> 00:25:09,765
You do so many activities,

327
00:25:09,766 --> 00:25:12,325
and you're so talented.

328
00:25:15,698 --> 00:25:20,411
Actually, I've had a crush on you too.

329
00:25:20,412 --> 00:25:24,626
At first, I thought it was just like a regular fan admiring you,

330
00:25:24,627 --> 00:25:26,612
like everyone else.

331
00:25:27,120 --> 00:25:28,248
But...

332
00:25:28,975 --> 00:25:32,772
after seeing you do so many things,

333
00:25:33,431 --> 00:25:37,321
I felt like I wanted to get to know you better.

334
00:25:39,097 --> 00:25:43,829
I'm glad you hit me in the face with that basketball that day.

335
00:25:43,830 --> 00:25:45,992
It gave us a chance to talk.

336
00:25:47,653 --> 00:25:50,668
And today you even came to talk to me first.

337
00:25:55,529 --> 00:25:59,023
I just wanted to tell you how I feel.

338
00:25:59,657 --> 00:26:05,115
Even if you already have someone you like, it's okay.

339
00:26:09,828 --> 00:26:11,558
Thank you so much.

340
00:26:11,805 --> 00:26:13,699
You're so cool, Aioon,

341
00:26:13,700 --> 00:26:15,740
for being brave enough to confess to me directly.

342
00:26:15,741 --> 00:26:18,365
I don't even have the courage to tell someone I like them directly like this.

343
00:26:19,395 --> 00:26:22,091
From now on, if you need my help with anything,

344
00:26:22,092 --> 00:26:26,027
or if you want some advice, you can reach out to me anytime, okay?

345
00:26:26,028 --> 00:26:27,879
Don't hesitate at all.

346
00:26:31,434 --> 00:26:34,245
Now, show me the video. I'll help you edit it.

347
00:26:34,246 --> 00:26:35,285
Okay!

348
00:27:00,560 --> 00:27:03,188
[@Nalin A student from Class 11C skipped school this afternoon.]

349
00:27:03,188 --> 00:27:06,199
[Teacher Nalin, were you not aware of this?]

350
00:27:12,043 --> 00:27:14,658
[Even though you are a new homeroom teacher,]

351
00:27:14,658 --> 00:27:17,458
[please take good care of your students.]

352
00:27:36,201 --> 00:27:37,345
I have exams coming up.

353
00:27:37,346 --> 00:27:40,587
Do you even study? Please, at least read a little.

354
00:27:42,475 --> 00:27:44,603
By the way, what should we eat?

355
00:27:46,382 --> 00:27:49,411
"Whatever" again? Then you choose.

356
00:27:51,872 --> 00:27:53,338
Not this one.

357
00:27:53,607 --> 00:27:55,073
Let's have something Japanese.

358
00:28:02,396 --> 00:28:03,858
Not this one.

359
00:28:05,119 --> 00:28:06,919
May I speak with Belle for a moment?

360
00:28:17,852 --> 00:28:19,406
If you're going to break the rules,

361
00:28:20,146 --> 00:28:21,932
why do it in a way where you get caught?

362
00:28:24,574 --> 00:28:26,502
Just in case you didn't know, teacher...

363
00:28:27,424 --> 00:28:29,919
I'm the Mother Superior's biological niece.

364
00:28:31,436 --> 00:28:32,916
That means...

365
00:28:33,291 --> 00:28:35,209
no matter how badly I behave,

366
00:28:35,210 --> 00:28:37,763
or how much I want to get expelled,

367
00:28:38,236 --> 00:28:39,945
my aunt will never expel me.

368
00:28:40,673 --> 00:28:43,588
So you don't need to care about me.

369
00:28:44,583 --> 00:28:46,443
Just leave it between me and my aunt.

370
00:28:49,365 --> 00:28:52,745
I don't care about your personal life.

371
00:28:58,963 --> 00:29:02,449
But I pity your skills.

372
00:29:02,450 --> 00:29:04,535
If you want the school to stop targeting you,

373
00:29:04,535 --> 00:29:10,332
prove yourself in the right way.

374
00:29:13,011 --> 00:29:16,471
I don't think I have to prove myself,

375
00:29:17,741 --> 00:29:20,496
especially in this stupid school.

376
00:29:20,696 --> 00:29:25,324
Do you really not know what freedom is?

377
00:29:25,325 --> 00:29:28,086
If you really want freedom,

378
00:29:28,087 --> 00:29:32,425
you wouldn't act in a way that makes people constantly try to control you.

379
00:29:32,878 --> 00:29:35,176
The more you act out,

380
00:29:35,177 --> 00:29:37,824
the more you're just demanding attention.

381
00:29:40,461 --> 00:29:42,890
I know that at this school,

382
00:29:43,122 --> 00:29:45,269
there are a lot of things that don't make sense.

383
00:29:45,584 --> 00:29:48,386
It's very different from your old school environment.

384
00:29:48,988 --> 00:29:50,468
Stop running away,

385
00:29:50,788 --> 00:29:53,654
and try to actually beat the Mother Superior, how about that?

386
00:29:55,342 --> 00:29:56,831
What do you mean?

387
00:29:56,831 --> 00:30:00,796
If you agree to compete in the French contest and win,

388
00:30:00,796 --> 00:30:02,949
I'll talk to the Mother Superior for you.

389
00:30:02,949 --> 00:30:05,029
I'll suggest she transfer you back to an international school

390
00:30:05,030 --> 00:30:06,980
where my friend teaches.

391
00:30:06,981 --> 00:30:09,306
There's a scholarship to study abroad.

392
00:30:09,774 --> 00:30:12,265
If you really want to escape your aunt,

393
00:30:12,805 --> 00:30:14,353
this is a great option.

394
00:30:14,726 --> 00:30:16,713
Or even if you don't want to go,

395
00:30:16,714 --> 00:30:20,730
it's an excuse with enough weight to make the Mother Superior

396
00:30:20,730 --> 00:30:22,397
accept you.

397
00:30:26,860 --> 00:30:30,254
And who are you? Why would my aunt listen to you?

398
00:30:31,328 --> 00:30:33,670
Before you can make the Mother Superior believe in you,

399
00:30:34,957 --> 00:30:36,397
you have to believe in me first.

400
00:30:52,519 --> 00:30:55,358
Do you have any plans for celebrating this Saturday?

401
00:30:57,115 --> 00:30:58,435
This Saturday?

402
00:31:00,298 --> 00:31:04,284
Don't tell me you studied so hard you forgot your own birthday.

403
00:31:05,698 --> 00:31:07,011
Oh.

404
00:31:07,298 --> 00:31:08,805
You're right.

405
00:31:08,918 --> 00:31:11,196
If you don't know where to go yet,

406
00:31:11,197 --> 00:31:15,105
should we go to my friend's resort? The one we went to last year.

407
00:31:16,029 --> 00:31:17,938
Sure, if you want to go.

408
00:31:18,499 --> 00:31:20,026
Invite Amy along too.

409
00:31:20,701 --> 00:31:24,934
It's your birthday, invite your close friend so you can have fun.

410
00:31:24,935 --> 00:31:27,597
And I can get to know Amy better too.

411
00:31:30,256 --> 00:31:31,683
Okay.

412
00:31:40,262 --> 00:31:41,997
I'm here.

413
00:31:44,374 --> 00:31:47,358
I told the doctor we can start the targeted therapy.

414
00:31:48,893 --> 00:31:51,041
And where did you get the money for that, honey?

415
00:31:53,605 --> 00:31:55,927
I have some savings.

416
00:32:03,908 --> 00:32:08,072
My illness is causing you so much trouble.

417
00:32:10,871 --> 00:32:12,464
Don't say that.

418
00:32:10,931 --> 00:32:15,687
What trouble?

419
00:32:15,687 --> 00:32:18,984
When I was a kid, I was sick all the time.

420
00:32:18,985 --> 00:32:21,028
And you never complained.

421
00:32:21,447 --> 00:32:23,631
But now I'm a grown-up.

422
00:32:24,191 --> 00:32:26,226
Anything I can do for you,

423
00:32:27,201 --> 00:32:29,143
please let me do it for you, Mom.

424
00:32:32,260 --> 00:32:36,423
I'll be getting a bonus from the school next month anyway.

425
00:32:37,332 --> 00:32:39,352
As for your medical bills,

426
00:32:40,027 --> 00:32:41,433
I can pay them no matter how much they are.

427
00:32:42,219 --> 00:32:43,786
Don't worry.

428
00:32:45,370 --> 00:32:46,883
Thank you, honey.

429
00:32:53,280 --> 00:32:54,527
You're such a good girl.

430
00:33:25,155 --> 00:33:26,355
Where's Teacher Nalin?

431
00:33:26,450 --> 00:33:28,323
She's probably not coming today.

432
00:33:28,324 --> 00:33:31,411
She said we'll start practicing when we have all 4 people.

433
00:33:35,168 --> 00:33:38,034
So you're here because...?

434
00:33:38,690 --> 00:33:40,670
Yeah, I entered the competition too.

435
00:33:40,831 --> 00:33:42,231
Whoa!

436
00:33:43,585 --> 00:33:45,098
What are you doing?

437
00:33:45,631 --> 00:33:47,395
Just scrolling through my feed.

438
00:33:53,407 --> 00:33:54,615
Is that Amy?

439
00:33:54,616 --> 00:33:57,728
Yeah, she's singing a Marc-Flute song.

440
00:33:58,332 --> 00:33:59,785
Marc-Flute?

441
00:34:00,893 --> 00:34:04,830
Oh, the ship you like, right?

442
00:34:05,199 --> 00:34:06,765
Yeah.

443
00:34:16,384 --> 00:34:21,587
[Even without seeing your face, I can't take it anymore.]

444
00:34:33,591 --> 00:34:35,191
You saw that, right?

445
00:34:37,624 --> 00:34:38,977
Yeah.

446
00:34:47,350 --> 00:34:49,740
Belle, can you please not tell anyone about this?

447
00:34:51,524 --> 00:34:54,830
Who would I even tell?

448
00:34:57,613 --> 00:34:59,233
I won't tell anyone anyway.

449
00:34:59,908 --> 00:35:03,532
But you probably think badly of me now, don't you?

450
00:35:06,331 --> 00:35:09,219
Why do you care how I look at you?

451
00:35:15,704 --> 00:35:17,896
What kind of person you are,

452
00:35:17,897 --> 00:35:19,772
you know yourself best.

453
00:35:20,531 --> 00:35:21,865
Have you heard that?

454
00:35:25,134 --> 00:35:30,024
In the end, whether people find out about this in the future or not,

455
00:35:31,097 --> 00:35:32,265
I think

456
00:35:32,519 --> 00:35:35,894
you know best what kind of person you are.

457
00:35:36,508 --> 00:35:38,221
That's the most important thing.

458
00:35:44,138 --> 00:35:45,617
And also...

459
00:35:46,716 --> 00:35:49,642
I've never seen you as a bad person.

460
00:35:51,175 --> 00:35:56,080
I've never met anyone who studies as hard as you.

461
00:35:56,480 --> 00:35:59,264
In this school, you're probably the most frugal person too.

462
00:36:02,523 --> 00:36:04,327
So I think...

463
00:36:05,719 --> 00:36:08,052
you making sex content,

464
00:36:09,140 --> 00:36:11,687
I think you must have your own reasons.

465
00:36:13,067 --> 00:36:16,040
If in the future someone bullies you saying

466
00:36:16,041 --> 00:36:17,759
you do this because you're hungry for money,

467
00:36:18,245 --> 00:36:19,559
tell me.

468
00:36:19,784 --> 00:36:21,518
I'll punch them in the face for you.

469
00:36:25,029 --> 00:36:26,383
Promise me?

470
00:36:26,845 --> 00:36:28,265
That you won't tell anyone.

471
00:36:31,010 --> 00:36:33,932
On the honor of the Mother Superior.

472
00:36:57,678 --> 00:37:01,148
And I'd be happy to hire you immediately.

473
00:37:04,084 --> 00:37:06,914
If you promise me one thing.

474
00:37:08,456 --> 00:37:09,789
What is it?

475
00:37:14,510 --> 00:37:17,914
I want you to get close to the students.

476
00:37:18,513 --> 00:37:20,841
Learn about their personal lives,

477
00:37:20,842 --> 00:37:24,150
or any bad behaviors they are secretly doing.

478
00:37:24,151 --> 00:37:25,704
And report back to me.

479
00:37:26,351 --> 00:37:31,021
So that we can eliminate the problem early on.

480
00:37:31,845 --> 00:37:33,640
But, Mother Superior,

481
00:37:33,641 --> 00:37:36,721
if we use our position as teachers to approach students

482
00:37:36,722 --> 00:37:38,523
with hidden agendas,

483
00:37:39,083 --> 00:37:42,100
isn't that a violation of the students' privacy?

484
00:37:42,501 --> 00:37:46,568
The parents have entrusted us to fully take care of their children.

485
00:37:46,884 --> 00:37:48,359
Therefore,

486
00:37:48,360 --> 00:37:51,784
if there's anything that could damage our school's reputation,

487
00:37:53,288 --> 00:37:56,011
we won't consider it

488
00:37:56,191 --> 00:37:58,828
a private matter for the students at all.

489
00:37:59,155 --> 00:38:01,723
You don't need to worry about anything.

490
00:38:04,995 --> 00:38:07,811
Will you accept my offer, Teacher Nalin?

491
00:38:16,085 --> 00:38:18,156
Well, Teacher Nalin?

492
00:38:18,157 --> 00:38:23,109
Are there any students at risk of ruining our school's reputation?

